  value = data.aws_caller_identity.current.account_id
}
ğŸ”¹ Read Terraform remote state
hcl
Copy
Edit
data "terraform_remote_state" "network" {
  backend = "s3"

  config = {
    bucket = "my-state-bucket"
    key    = "network/terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-1"
  }
}
ğŸš« Data Sources Don't Create Resources
Unlike resource blocks, data blocks donâ€™t provision anything â€” they just fetch info.

ğŸ”’ Best Practices
Avoid hardcoding values â€” use data to dynamically fetch them

Use data.terraform_remote_state for multi-stack infrastructure

Combine with locals or output for better reuse